OL,3,CWife mistakes husband's cardiac arrest
OL,4,Cfor snoring
OL,6,FWhen paramedics from South Central
OL,7,FAmbulance arrived, they confirmed
OL,8,FBarry was suffering a cardiac arrest.
OL,9,FHe needed six shocks with a
OL,10,Fdefibrillator to bring him back to
OL,11,Flife.
OL,13,FThe sounds Alison had been woken up by
OL,14,Fwas in fact agonal breathing ` a
OL,15,Fcommon occurrence in people suffering
OL,16,Fa cardiac arrest when a lack of oxygen
OL,17,Fcauses a gasping effect.
OL,19,FBarry subsequently underwent double
OL,20,Fheart bypass surgery at the Royal
OL,21,FBrompton Hospital.
